Speaker 2: You beat me to it.

Speaker 1: How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Well, I was just wondering.

Speaker 1: I remember at one point, you know, I was on the phone with you and you said that you wanted—

Speaker 2: To talk to me.

Speaker 1: And I was like, well, I don't know.

Speaker 2: I don't want to talk to you.

Speaker 1: Absolutely.

Speaker 2: I'm looking at your chart now.

Speaker 1: So let's see how much I got.

Speaker 2: So that was in July of last year, you got a quantity of 50 D-Alice, 20 milligrams.

Speaker 1: I'm just curious why, hold on, let me check on the back end.

Speaker 2: My question is, because I remember that, again, I don't know if it was Angel or John—

Speaker 1: But they were just really inappropriate in saying, okay, well, you know, if you switch—

Speaker 2: You can never change back.

Speaker 1: Are you sure you want to do that?

Speaker 2: Raise your right hand and swear to God.

Speaker 1: It's just like, you know, you shouldn't make people feel like that because from my perspective—

Speaker 2: What I'm thinking is, I remember I was able to get that and it wasn't like I had to wait—

Speaker 1: A hundred days until I could get another one.

Speaker 2: It was like I'm now considering the fact of, because it seems like the AGV is in such short—

Speaker 1: Supply or something that maybe I should go back to C-Alice because at least I can get—

Speaker 2: You know, a 30-day supply every 30 days or something, you know?

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: Is that what I feel?

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: Yeah.

Speaker 1: Yeah.

Speaker 2: I'm just reading over your hand.

Speaker 1: Yeah, it's just not doable on the rations that I'm being given, you know?

Speaker 2: This is not even a controlled substance, you know?

Speaker 1: I mean, I'm a physician.

Speaker 2: I myself prescribe Adderall and things like that, and those are controlled substances—

Speaker 1: Which require monitoring and checking and, you know, making sure that a person doesn't—

Speaker 2: But I mean, you know, for everything else I prescribe, this is ridiculous.

Speaker 1: I'm just being rationed and I'm, it's really affecting me because as I told you with the—

Speaker 2: Problem with my girlfriend, I have to really guess correctly all the time in order for—

Speaker 1: Me not to run out, and I can't guess correctly all the time because sometimes I think I'm—

Speaker 2: Going to get it and I don't, but sometimes, you know, I don't know.

Speaker 1: So would I be able to get it more frequently if I did the Cialis instead of the AGV?

Speaker 2: No, I'm sure we can work something out with the AGV.

Speaker 1: I, again, am going to place you on a brief hold and go speak to one of my supervisors—

Speaker 2: About this, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Thank you.
